and women’s obligations and duties in a marital partnership; how the Charter has come to be perceived by men and women especially in its enforcement in the context of divorce; and the social repercussions of the Charter on the family in its application. There has been ongoing discussion on the implications of the Charter on the lives of Singaporean women and men for some years since its implementation. The purpose of this book is to enrich our understanding of this legislation further — its objectives, efficacy and shortfalls.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aWomenxLegal status, laws, etc.zSingapore. 0aWomen's rightszSingapore. 0aWomen's rights--Singapore. 0aWomen--Legal status, Laws, etc.--Singapore. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aDevasahayam, Theresa W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDevasahayam, Theresa W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKoh, Tommy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKum, Leong Wai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Ellen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNair, Sudha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoin, Kanwaljit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWee, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102470708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z